        "name": "Experiment 4: Stability Radius Certification and Numerical Error Bounds",
        "description": "For each layer assigned INT8 or FP16 precision, compute formal bounds on numerical error propagation: (1) Quantize layer weights/activations, (2) Measure actual output perturbation (L2 distance between FP32 and quantized outputs), (3) Compare to theoretical stability radius derived from condition number and precision level. Formally define: Δ_FP16 = κ · 2^(-10) (approx. FP16 epsilon), Δ_INT8 = κ · 2^(-8). Verify that empirical perturbations stay within predicted bounds across 1000 test samples. Compute tightness ratio (empirical error / theoretical bound) to quantify conservatism. Report failure rate (% of samples exceeding bound) and provide explicit error certificates per layer.",
